<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,906,1941]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1879,1905]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is from the Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[762,843,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">nigrum</emphasis>
”—black, and “ 
<emphasis box="[1018,1069,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">stria</emphasis>
”—stripe, and refers to the black longitudinal striae characteristic of the species.
</paragraph>
